parameters.content:
## Core Trigger Nodes

**Manual Trigger** - Manually start workflows for testing and one-time executions

**Schedule Trigger** - Automatically run workflows on a time-based schedule (hourly, daily, weekly, etc.)

**Google Drive Trigger** - Monitor Google Drive folders for file changes and trigger workflows automatically

parameters.content:
## Data Processing Nodes

**Create Sample Data** - Generate mock JSON data for testing and development

**Split Users Array** - Break down arrays into individual items for processing

**Aggregate** - Combine and summarize data from multiple items

**Edit Fields** - Transform data by adding, modifying, or extracting specific fields

**If** - Create conditional logic to route data based on specific criteria

**Code** - Execute custom JavaScript for complex data transformations

## Connectivity and API Nodes

**Webhook** - Receive HTTP requests from external services to trigger workflows

**Respond to Webhook** - Send HTTP responses back to webhook callers

**HTTP Request** - Make API calls to external services and retrieve data

## Storage Nodes

**Upload file (Google Drive)** - Store files and documents in Google Drive cloud storage

**Create spreadsheet (Google Sheets)** - Generate and manage spreadsheets for data organization

**Insert rows in a table (Postgres)** - Store structured data in PostgreSQL databases

## AI Nodes

**AI Agent** - Autonomous AI that can use tools and make decisions to complete complex tasks

**Basic LLM Chain** - Simple language model interface for text generation and analysis
